-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

Binary files are not just unreadable garbage. They often contain readable strings embedded inside them, including flags in CTF challenges.

The strings command is one of the first tools you should reach for in any reverse engineering challenge. Always try it early.

grep is your best friend for searching through large outputs. Instead of reading thousands of lines, pipe into grep and filter instantly.

The pipe symbol | is one of the most powerful concepts in Linux. Chaining commands together lets you build powerful one-liners that would otherwise take many steps.

wget is how you download files in the terminal without opening a browser.
